## Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.10+
- Node.js 18+
- OpenAI API key

### 1. Clone & Setup Backend

```bash
git clone https://github.com/daksh-lgtm/GEO_workflow.git
cd GEO_workflow/project

# Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Create .env file
echo "OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here" > .env

# Create data folder
mkdir -p data

# Run backend
uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000
```

Backend is live at `http://localhost:8000`  
Swagger docs at `http://localhost:8000/docs`

### 2. Setup Frontend

```bash
cd ../frontend

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start dev server
npm start
```

Frontend is live at `http://localhost:3000`

### 3. Analyze a Product

1. Open `http://localhost:3000`
2. Paste any product URL (Amazon, Flipkart, Gymshark, IKEA...)
3. Click **Analyze** вҖ” GENY crawls + scores in ~10s
4. Review the AI Visibility Score (arc gauge + 5 bars)
5. Click **GEO Optimize Now** вҖ” 4 agents run in ~45вҖ“90s
6. Get your full report with exact copy-paste fixes

---

## API Reference

### `POST /crawl_product`
Crawls a product page and saves raw data.

```json
// Request
{ "url": "https://www.gymshark.com/products/power-cut-off-tank" }

// Response
{
  "message": "Product crawled successfully",
  "saved_to": "data/gymshark-com-products-...-20250221.json",
  "product_name": "Power Cut Off Tank",
  "url": "https://www.gymshark.com/products/power-cut-off-tank"
}
```

### `POST /geo_context`
Scores the crawled page and builds LLM context.

```json
// Request
{ "filename": "gymshark-com-products-...-20250221.json" }

// Response
{
  "ai_readiness_pct": 58.0,
  "readiness_band": "Fair вҖ” Needs Improvement",
  "llm_context": {
    "ai_visibility_summary": { "final_score": 58, "max_possible": 100 },
    "section_scores": { "schema": 18, "entity": 9, "content": 14, "trust": 11, "extractability": 6 },
    "weak_areas": { "entity": ["category","gtin"], "extractability": ["canonical_url","hreflang"] },
    "priority_order": ["extractability", "entity", "content", "trust", "schema"]
  }
}
```

### `POST /geo_recommendation`
Runs the 4-agent LangGraph pipeline.

```json
// Request
{ "filename": "gymshark-com-products-...-20250221.json" }

// Response
{
  "executive_summary": "The Gymshark Power Cut Off Tank scores 58/100...",
  "technical_analysis": "## Missing Canonical URL\n**Why it matters...",
  "content_analysis":   "### Missing Specifications Table\n...",
  "prioritized_plan":   "### Quick Wins\n| # | Change | Score gain |...",
  "ai_readiness_pct": 58.0,
  "readiness_band": "Fair вҖ” Needs Improvement"
}
```

---

## Frontend Phases

The React app has 5 phases with distinct UI for each:

```
input        вҶ’  URL entry, GENY hero, example pills
crawling     вҶ’  7-step progress indicator, SpinLoader
score        вҶ’  ScoreArc gauge + 5 ScoreBars + breakdown cards + GEO CTA
geo_loading  вҶ’  Radar animation + 4-agent pipeline + live data stream + insight carousel
geo_done     вҶ’  Product banner + 4 GeoCards (Executive/Technical/Content/Priority)
```

---

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Required | Description |
|----------|----------|-------------|
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | вң… Yes | Your OpenAI API key |
| `REACT_APP_API_URL` | вң… Production | Backend URL for deployed frontend |

**Never commit your `.env` file.** GitHub will block the push and your key is compromised.

---

## Deployment

### Backend вҶ’ Railway

```bash
# In project/ root вҖ” make sure these exist:
# requirements.txt  (pip freeze > requirements.txt)
# Procfile          (web: uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT)

# Push to GitHub, then:
# Railway вҶ’ New Project вҶ’ Deploy from GitHub вҶ’ Add OPENAI_API_KEY variable
```

### Frontend вҶ’ Vercel

```bash
cd frontend
vercel

# In Vercel dashboard вҶ’ Settings вҶ’ Environment Variables:
# REACT_APP_API_URL = https://your-app.railway.app
```

Update CORS in `main.py` to include your Vercel URL:
```python
allow_origins=[
    "http://localhost:3000",
    "https://your-app.vercel.app",
    "https://*.vercel.app"
]
```

